- Initial solution structure with core library, contracts, and models projects.
- Optimizely CMS integration via URL resolver pipeline steps, partial routers, and a controller for virtual text rendering.
- Azure Table storage integration for virtual file locations and Azure Blob storage integration for virtual file content.
- Service collection and application builder extensions to register and wire up the VirtualText services.
- Models and options for virtual file locations, routed data, and configuration defaults.
- Build, packaging, and repository scaffolding (GitVersion, Directory.Packages.props, NuGet config, CI, license, and contributing docs).
